  "_comment": [
    "Golden vectors for the PDF report's computed dataset.",
    "Read by BOTH suites: ReportDataTests (Swift) and ReportDataVectorTest (Kotlin).",
    "",
    "SCOPE, AND WHY IT IS NOT THE WHOLE STRUCT.",
    "  Android's PdfReportData.from() reads the device time zone, the device locale",
    "  and the real clock. Its hour-of-day profile, its weekday columns and its",
    "  abstinence streaks therefore cannot be pinned from a file without rebuilding",
    "  the Kotlin signature. What IS pinned here is everything independent of those",
    "  three: the period, the totals, the medians, the monthly table, the category",
    "  breakdown, the peaks, and the count of days over the daily limit.",
    "",
    "  The Swift side covers the remaining fields in ReportDataTests, where the zone,",
    "  the locale and today are injected. Where a figure can be shared, it is shared.",
    "",
    "Entries carry only what these figures need: an id, a drink, a logical date and",
    "the grams. Timestamps are irrelevant to every value below.",
    "",
    "Vectors encode CURRENT behaviour. Changing one changes both platforms."
  ],
